# Because I'm paranoid and because I want to see untracked files, I maintain
# an exhaustive gitignore list. This also makes searching my home directory
# with ripgrep convenient, since it won't descend into most directories.

# We start by un-ignoring all hidden files and directories. This way, hidden
# directories like `.config` will show up in ripgrep searches.
#
# This does mean that `.git` gets whitelisted, which isn't what we want. So we
# ignore it in `~/.ignore`.
!.*

# This is my syncthing directory.
/sync

# top-level hidden files/directories that we specifically ignore and skip over.
# It's annoying to maintain this list, but it's worth doing IMO. Because it
# lets us craft a small(ish) `$HOME` environment that works well with tools
# that respect `.gitignore` outside of `git`.
